                <h1>Understanding FCRA Compliance: A Quick Guide</h1>
                <p>FCRA compliance refers to adherence to the Fair Credit Reporting Act, which regulates the collection, dissemination, and use of consumer information, ensuring individuals’ privacy and accuracy in their credit reports. Compliance involves practices like transparent reporting, fair use of data, and providing consumers with access to their information.</p>
